<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5019832>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 64–69. Genitalia of Atheta modesta (Melsheimer) (male, Lac Lapêche, Québec (64– 66); male, paralectotype of At. vierecki Casey (67–68); and female, 8 km SEE Springfield, Vermont (69)). 64 — median lobe with retracted internal sac, parameral view; 65 — median lobe with retracted internal sac, abparameral view; 66 — median lobe with retracted internal sac, lateral view; 67 — apex of median lobe with everted internal sac, parameral view; 68 — median lobe with everted internal sac, lateral view; 69 — spermatheca. Scale bar 0.2 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/5019832/files/figure.png" .

